Question: Create a small calculator which only does ‘+’ or ‘-‘ Operations.
(Hint: Take three variable inputs with one being used for the operator)

START
PRINT "Enter two numbers"
INPUT x
INPUT y
PRINT "Enter the operator"
PRINT "+ to add and - to subtract the numbers"
INPUT oper
IF (oper == +)
  PRINT "{x+y}"
ELSE IF (oper == -)
  PRINT "{x-y}"
ELSE
  PRINT "<!> INVALID OPERATOR <!>"
END
